HEADWORD: Perspectograph
<hw>Per*spec"to*graph</hw>
<pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*sp⟦ecr⟧k"t⟦osl⟧*gr⟦adot⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>perspectus</ets> (p. p. of <ets>perspicere</ets> to look through) +
<ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>An instrument for obtaining, and
transferring to a picture, the points and outlines of objects, so as to
represent them in their proper geometrical relations as viewed from some
one point.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Perspectography</ent>⟦br⟧
